Class AbstractHugeHashSet<E>

  • java.lang.Object

  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>, java.util.Set<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HugeHashSet, ImmutableHugeHashSet

    public abstract class AbstractHugeHashSet<E>
extends java.util.AbstractSet<E>
    An abstract base class to simplify implementing a huge Set that mimics a HashSet.

    The mutating operations are implemented as protected methods with the suffix "Internal".

    • addInternal(E)
    • removeInternal(Object)
    • clearInternal()

    Immutable concrete subclasses can call these internal methods to implement a builder.

    Mutable concrete subclasses can implement the equivalent public methods by calling the internal methods.

      • addInternal

        protected boolean addInternal(E element)
        Adds an element.

        This method has the same semantics as AbstractCollection.add(Object). Mutable subclasses can implement AbstractCollection.add(Object) by calling this method.

        Immutable subclasses can call this method from the builder.

        Parameters:
        element - the element to add
        Returns:
        true if the element was added, false otherwise
